<H2><CENTER><FONT FACE="Arial"><A NAME=book></A>My Book: "Antonio
Meucci - L'inventore e il suo tempo"</FONT></CENTER></H2>

<CENTER><FONT FACE="Arial"><IMG SRC="immagini/mybook.jpg" WIDTH=414 HEIGHT=253 X-CLARIS-USEIMAGEWIDTH X-CLARIS-USEIMAGEHEIGHT ALIGN=bottom></FONT></CENTER>

<P><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">Basilio Catania's book
"Antonio Meucci - L'inventore e il suo tempo" ("Antonio Meucci - The
Inventor and His Times"), Vols. 1 and 2, in Italian, cannot be
purchased anymore from Libreria Editrice Universitaria
</FONT><A HREF="http://WWW.LEVROTTO-BELLA.NET/"><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">Levrotto
&amp; Bella</FONT></A><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">,
because all of the copies have been sold. An English translation of
the textual part of the book, is available on CD-ROM, by writing to
the author, at the mere shipping and CD-masterizing cost.<BR>
A review of the book is available on the Web, in Italian, at the site
</FONT><A HREF="http://www.italians-world.org/altreitalie/16_Libri0.htm"><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">Altreitalie</FONT></A><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">
(a magazine from Fondazione Agnelli for the Italians in the world)
and is also reproduced </FONT><A HREF="#Altreitalie_review"><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">below</FONT></A><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">.<BR>
Another review of the book, in Spanish, is authored by
</FONT><A HREF="http://www.ub.es/geocrit/altshule.htm"><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">Prof.
Jos&eacute; Altshuler</FONT></A><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">
and was published in the Newsletter of the Sociedad Cubana de
Historia de la Ciencia y la Tecnolog&iacute;a, as well as in the
Revista de la Sociedad Espa&ntilde;ola de Historia de la Ciencias y
la T&eacute;cnicas (LLULL), and it is also reported </FONT><A HREF="#Altshuler_review"><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">below</FONT></A><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Times New Roman">.<BR>
Tablets honoring Antonio Meucci as the inventor of the telephone were
inaugurated in Florence in 1996 and in Havana in 1997, following the
findings in Basilio Catania's book.<BR>
The above book is now (beginning of 2001) available from both the
<I>Library of Congress</I> and the <I>New York Public Library</I> at
the following locations:</FONT></P>

